data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/lina-khan-ftc-confirmation-antitrust-big-tech-183254782.html">联邦贸易委员会主席莉娜·汗</a>、委员丽贝卡·凯利·斯劳特和阿尔瓦罗·贝多亚进行会谈。此次谈话被视为“最后仪式”会议，为该公司提供了最后一次机会，在提交决定之前说服政府机构做出让步。预计的诉讼将对该公司涉嫌反竞争行为的为期四年的调查推向高潮。它还面临一项单独的联邦贸易委员会诉讼，涉及<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/ftc-sues-amazon-for-allegedly-tricking-customers-into-prime-subscriptions-151528914.html">欺骗客户订阅 Prime 服务</a>。</p><p>据报道，联邦贸易委员会的部分兴趣在于亚马逊与第三方卖家的交易，这是反垄断争论中长期以来的焦点。 《<em>华尔街日报》</em>在 2020 年报道称，亚马逊员工<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/us-lawmakers-ask-jeff-bezos-to-testify-154908160.html">使用第三方卖家的内部数据</a>来创建内部产品。这导致该公司同意停止在搜索结果中提升其内部品牌，从而使它们更难销售。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/amazon-is-reportedly-cutting-most-of-its-in-house-clothing-brands-175110764.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/amazon-is-reportedly-cutting-most-of-its-in-house-clothing-brands-175110764.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> e7909ade-62a7-4d76-bf21-7cce5c026f91</guid><dc:creator>威尔·尚克林</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 10 Aug 2023 17:51:10 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1691689872</ingested><modified> 2023-08-10T17:51:23+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Business]]></category><category><![CDATA[Company Legal & Law Matters]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Will Shanklin]]></category><media:content height="3695" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/63ece610-1072-11ee-a7a0-fd30e9f1176b" width="5629"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]